      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: handle Claude CLI synthetic placeholders",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #90789 by recognizing Claude Code CLI synthetic assistant placeholders as CLI-generated no-output metadata instead of treating the turn as an ordinary empty result.\n\nThis covers the observed `model: \"<synthetic>\"` assistant events with:\n\n- `No response requested.`\n- `Continue from where you left off.`\n\n## What changed\n\n- Detect Claude stream-json assistant records where `message.model === \"<synthetic>\"` and the text exactly matches a known Claude CLI placeholder.\n- Preserve a `syntheticPlaceholder` marker across both buffered JSONL parsing and streaming parsing, including when a later empty `type: \"result\"` event arrives.\n- Propagate that marker into embedded run metadata as `terminalReplyKind: \"synthetic-placeholder\"`.\n- **Make the classifier path reachable from `runPreparedCliAgent`**: `executeCliAttempt` previously threw `FailoverError(empty_response)` on every empty-text turn, swallowing the synthetic marker before `buildCliRunResult` could surface it. The throw is now skipped when `output.syntheticPlaceholder === true`, so the run result keeps `terminalReplyKind` and the classifier returns the richer `empty_result` verdict.\n- Classify synthetic-placeholder terminal replies as fallback-worthy `empty_result` for model fallback / observability, including non-GPT models such as `claude-cli/Claude-Opus-4.7`.\n- Keep explicit OpenClaw silent replies (`NO_REPLY`) out of fallback behavior.\n\n## Rationale\n\nThe placeholder is generated by the CLI/runtime, not by the assistant and not by OpenClaw's explicit silent-reply contract. Surfacing it as a normal reply would be wrong, but silently swallowing it can leave Telegram/group-chat turns with no visible message and no useful recovery path. Treating it as an empty-result classification preserves observability and allows existing fallback handling to recover.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/cli-output.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/result-fallback-classifier.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner.context-engine.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner.synthetic-placeholder.test.ts`\n  - 4 files passed, 50 tests passed\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/agents/cli-output.ts src/agents/cli-output.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner.ts src/agents/cli-runner.synthetic-placeholder.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/result-fallback-classifier.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/result-fallback-classifier.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/types.ts`\n  - 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt src/agents/cli-runner.ts src/agents/cli-runner.synthetic-placeholder.test.ts`\n  - clean\n- `git diff --check`\n  - clean\n\nNew `src/agents/cli-runner.synthetic-placeholder.test.ts` drives `runPreparedCliAgent` end-to-end with a mocked CLI output carrying `syntheticPlaceholder: true`, asserting both that `terminalReplyKind` reaches the result metadata and that `classifyEmbeddedAgentRunResultForModelFallback` emits the `empty_result` verdict — the integration coverage ClawSweeper P1 asked for.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Claude Code CLI emits a `<synthetic>` assistant placeholder (`No response requested.` / `Continue from where you left off.`) followed by an empty `type: \"result\"` event when its loop is wedged/timed-out. Before this fix, OpenClaw's `executeCliAttempt` saw the empty text and threw a generic `FailoverError(empty_response)` which left no `terminalReplyKind` metadata and no synthetic-placeholder signal for the model-fallback classifier, so the affected Telegram turn went silent with no recovery path (issue #90789).\n- **Real environment tested**: local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/wanglu241/code/openclaw`, branch `fix/90789-claude-cli-synthetic-placeholder` (head `8d6f1a7a`), node v26.0.0, pnpm/tsx 4.22.3, macOS 25.4.0 arm64. Parser + classifier executed against the real source via `pnpm exec tsx`, with the exact JSONL byte sequence the CLI emits (taken from `src/agents/cli-output.test.ts`'s captured fixture).\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  1. Build a one-off harness (`scratch/synthetic-placeholder-proof.ts`) that calls `parseCliJsonl(...)` with the synthetic-placeholder stream-json sequence and then invokes `classifyEmbeddedAgentRunResultForModelFallback(...)` against the resulting run-result shape.\n  2. Check out the upstream/main versions of `src/agents/cli-output.ts`, `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/result-fallback-classifier.ts`, and `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/types.ts`; run the harness; record output.\n  3. Restore the PR head versions of those files; run the harness again; record output.\n  4. Restore working tree, run `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/cli-runner.synthetic-placeholder.test.ts` to drive the same flow through `runPreparedCliAgent` end-to-end.\n- **Evidence after fix** (redacted terminal output from `pnpm exec tsx scratch/synthetic-placeholder-proof.ts`):\n\n```text\n=== BASELINE: upstream/main (no synthetic placeholder handling) ===\n---- parser output ----\n{\n  \"text\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"redacted-session\",\n  \"usage\": {\n    \"input\": 8\n  }\n}\n---- classifier verdict ----\nnull\n\n=== CANDIDATE: PR fix/90789-claude-cli-synthetic-placeholder ===\n---- parser output ----\n{\n  \"text\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"redacted-session\",\n  \"usage\": {\n    \"input\": 8\n  },\n  \"syntheticPlaceholder\": true\n}\n---- classifier verdict ----\n{\n  \"message\": \"claude-cli/Claude-Opus-4.7 ended with a synthetic placeholder and no visible assistant reply\",\n  \"reason\": \"format\",\n  \"code\": \"empty_result\"\n}\n```\n\nEnd-to-end `runPreparedCliAgent` integration test live output (`node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/cli-runner.synthetic-placeholder.test.ts`):\n\n```text\n RUN  v4.1.7 /Users/wanglu241/code/openclaw\n\n ✓ |agents| src/agents/cli-runner.synthetic-placeholder.test.ts (2 tests) 3.04s\n   ✓ runPreparedCliAgent synthetic-placeholder propagation > marks runs with synthetic-placeholder terminal reply kind and triggers empty_result fallback\n   ✓ runPreparedCliAgent synthetic-placeholder propagation > does not mark ordinary CLI runs and leaves the classifier null\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  2 passed (2)\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: with the PR applied, the JSONL parser surfaces `syntheticPlaceholder: true` (baseline does not), the run result carries `terminalReplyKind: \"synthetic-placeholder\"` (baseline strips it), and the model-fallback classifier returns `{ reason: \"format\", code: \"empty_result\", message: \"...synthetic placeholder...\" }` (baseline returns `null`). Downstream model-fallback machinery therefore now sees a fallback-worthy outcome instead of a silent turn for the wedge-aborted Claude CLI case from #90789.\n- **What was not tested**: Native Telegram Desktop capture under Crabbox could not exercise this code path because the bundled `extensions/qa-lab` mock provider does not (yet) emit `<synthetic>` stream-json events to OpenClaw — that is why the workflow's `Run agentic native Telegram proof` job posted a `comparison.status: skipped, pass: false` capture-infrastructure manifest. Adding mock-provider support for synthetic-placeholder injection is tracked as an out-of-scope follow-up; the live tsx run above and the new `runPreparedCliAgent` integration test cover the same code path end-to-end at the runtime layer.\n\n## Out-of-scope follow-ups\n\n- Teach `extensions/qa-lab` mock providers to optionally emit Claude CLI `<synthetic>` placeholder stream-json so the Mantis Telegram Desktop scenario can produce a native before/after recording for this fix.\n",
